Before creating a new component in Figma, **check if it already exists**. For example, if you need a button, look for the `Button` component.

Avoid manually adding `className` with styles such as `border-radius` (`rounded-md`), `color` (`text-white`, `text-gray-800`), `background-color` (`bg-blue-600`, `bg-red-500`), `padding` (`px-4`, `py-2`, `p-3`), `font-size` (`text-sm`, `text-lg`), etc., if these styles are **already included in the component** (e.g., `Button`) through its variants â€” they are **already part of the internally generated `className`**.

